---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
---

<Article
  title="Best Terraforming Mars Expansions Ranked"
  description="Prelude, Colonies, Venus Next — which TM expansions are worth buying and in what order?"
  game="terraforming-mars"
  gameTitle="Terraforming Mars"
  category="Buying Guide"
  publishDate="2025-05-06"
>
  <p>
    Terraforming Mars has five major expansions. Some are essential quality-of-life
    improvements, others add complexity that not everyone wants. Here's the order
    to buy them.
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="Buy Prelude first — it solves the slow start problem and is almost universally loved. Colonies is a great second expansion. Venus Next and Turmoil are optional and add significant complexity." />

  <div class="my-8 space-y-6">
    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-emerald-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">#1 ESSENTIAL</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🚀</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Prelude</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">The must-have expansion</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Faster Start</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Prelude Cards</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Adds Prelude cards that give you a jumpstart — extra production, resources, or terraforming
        at the start. The base game's first 2–3 generations can feel slow and samey. Prelude fixes
        this entirely. Every player immediately has a direction.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-blue-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">#2 HIGHLY RECOMMENDED</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🪐</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Colonies</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">New resource trade routes</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-purple-50 text-purple-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Trade Routes</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Resource Variety</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Adds colony moons you can trade with for resources. Gives you something productive to do
        when you can't afford expensive cards. The trade mechanic is simple to learn but adds
        meaningful decisions every generation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">♀️</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Venus Next</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">4th global parameter</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Adds Venus as a 4th global parameter to terraform. More cards, more paths to victory,
        but also makes the game longer. Good if your group wants more variety; skip if game
        length is already a concern.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🏛️</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Turmoil</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">Political system</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Adds a political layer with parties, delegates, and global events. The most complex
        expansion — it can feel like a second game layered on top. Only for groups that have
        mastered everything else and want more strategic depth.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-3">
        <InfoBox type="warning">
          Turmoil adds 30–45 minutes to game length and significant rules overhead. Most casual groups skip it. It's best for dedicated 2-player or experienced 3-player sessions.
        </InfoBox>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🗺️</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Hellas & Elysium</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">Alternate maps</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60">
        Two new Mars maps with different bonus placements and milestones/awards. A simple way
        to add variety without adding rules complexity. Get this whenever you want fresh
        geography — no wrong time to add it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <InfoBox type="tip" title="The Recommended Setup">
    <strong>Base game + Prelude + Colonies</strong> is the sweet spot for most groups. It solves the slow-start problem, adds meaningful decisions, and doesn't overstay its welcome. Add the Hellas/Elysium maps when you want fresh boards.
  </InfoBox>
</Article>
